# GUI Phase 1 — Technical Summary

**Commit:** `8e9715f` — _WIP: GUI – Phase 1 — Electron Skeleton + Tray + Detail View_

---

## Overview

Phase 1 delivers a working Electron tray app that reads existing syncthis-managed folders (initialized via CLI) and renders their status in a dashboard. It establishes the full architecture — process model, IPC layer, design system, i18n — that all subsequent phases build on.

**What works after Phase 1:**

- System tray icon with live status (idle / syncing / warning / error)
- Tray popover: folder list with health badges, sync-now, open dashboard
- Dashboard Detail View: status, info grid, activity-less action bar (start/stop/sync now/open/remove)
- Sidebar (appears at ≥ 2 folders)
- Light + dark mode following system preference
- CLI bundled to `~/.syncthis/bin/syncthis` on first launch

**Not included:** Setup wizard, GitHub OAuth, conflict resolution, settings UI, activity log, notifications, update check.

