## Monorepo changes

Two new packages added under `packages/`:

| Package | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `packages/shared` | Shared TypeScript types (config, health, IPC) used by both CLI and GUI |
| `packages/gui` | Electron app (this package) |

### Root `package.json` — new scripts

```json
"dev:cli":   "npm run dev -w packages/cli",
"dev:gui":   "npm run dev -w packages/gui",
"start:gui": "npm run start -w packages/gui",
"make:gui":  "npm run make -w packages/gui"
```

Typecheck now covers all three packages in sequence (shared must build before CLI/GUI typecheck):

```json
"typecheck": "npm run typecheck -w packages/shared && npm run typecheck -w packages/cli && npx tsc --noEmit -p packages/gui/tsconfig.json"
```

### CLI changes

- `packages/cli/src/config.ts` — `readConfig` and `writeConfig` now accept an optional `dirPath` argument so the GUI can read/write config for any folder, not just `process.cwd()`.
- `packages/cli/tsconfig.json` — set `composite: true` to support TypeScript project references from `packages/shared`.
- `packages/cli/package.json` — added `@syncthis/shared: "*"` dependency (workspace ref).

