## `packages/shared`

Extracts type definitions shared between CLI and GUI.

```
packages/shared/src/
├── config.types.ts       — SyncthisConfig, ConflictStrategy
├── health.types.ts       — HealthStatus, HealthLevel, ServiceStatus
├── ipc.types.ts          — IpcChannels, IpcEvents, FolderSummary, FolderDetail, …
├── json-output.types.ts  — JsonOutput (CLI --json response shape)
└── index.ts              — re-exports all types
```

### Key types

**`SyncthisConfig`**

```typescript
interface SyncthisConfig {
  remote: string;
  branch: string;
  cron: string | null;
  interval: number | null;
  daemonLabel?: string | null;
  autostart?: boolean;
  onConflict: ConflictStrategy;  // 'auto-both' | 'auto-newest' | 'ask' | 'stop'
  notify?: boolean;
}
```

**`HealthStatus`**

```typescript
interface HealthStatus {
  dirPath: string;
  level: HealthLevel;          // 'healthy' | 'degraded' | 'unhealthy'
  lastSync: string | null;     // ISO timestamp
  uptime: number | null;
  consecutiveFailures: number;
  syncCycles: number;
  serviceRunning: boolean;
}
```

**`IpcChannels` / `IpcEvents`** — full typed IPC contract (see `ipc.types.ts`). Phase 1 implements a subset; remaining channels are stubbed for future phases.

### Build setup

`tsconfig.json` uses `composite: true` so downstream packages can reference it via TypeScript project references. Build script: `tsc --build --force` (forces full rebuild to avoid stale cache issues from `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo`).

