## `packages/gui` — Preload

### `preload.ts`

Exposes a typed API to the renderer via `contextBridge`. No Node.js APIs leak directly.

```typescript
window.syncthis = {
  invoke<K extends keyof IpcChannels>(
    channel: K,
    args: IpcChannels[K]['args']
  ): Promise<IpcChannels[K]['result']>

  on<K extends keyof IpcEvents>(
    event: K,
    callback: (data: IpcEvents[K]) => void
  ): () => void  // returns unsubscribe function
}
```

Type declarations in `src/renderer/types/window.d.ts` extend `Window` so TypeScript knows about `window.syncthis` in renderer code.

