## i18n

All user-facing strings go through `t()`. Zero hardcoded strings in components.

**`src/renderer/i18n/en.json`** — 50+ keys:

```json
{
  "status.healthy": "Healthy",
  "status.degraded": "Degraded",
  "status.unhealthy": "Unhealthy",
  "status.service_stopped": "Service stopped",
  "status.synced_ago": "Synced {time} ago",
  "action.sync_now": "Sync now",
  "action.start": "Start syncing",
  "action.stop": "Stop syncing",
  "conflict_mode.auto_both": "Keep both versions",
  "conflict_mode.auto_newest": "Keep newest",
  "conflict_mode.ask": "Ask me",
  ...
}
```

**`src/renderer/i18n/index.ts`**

```typescript
export function t(key: TranslationKey, vars?: Record<string, string | number>): string {
  let str = en[key] ?? key;
  if (vars) for (const [k, v] of Object.entries(vars)) str = str.replace(`{${k}}`, String(v));
  return str;
}
```

`TranslationKey` is derived from `keyof typeof en`, so missing/typo'd keys are caught at compile time.

