## Utility functions

### `format-time.ts`

**`formatRelativeTime(isoString)`** — converts ISO timestamp to human-readable relative time:

| Elapsed | Output |
|---------|--------|
| < 10s | "just now" |
| < 60s | "30 seconds ago" |
| < 2min | "1 minute ago" |
| < 60min | "5 minutes ago" |
| < 2h | "1 hour ago" |
| < 24h | "3 hours ago" |
| otherwise | "2 days ago" |

**`formatSchedule(config)`** — converts `interval` (minutes) or `cron` string to human label:

| Value | Output |
|-------|--------|
| `interval: 1` | "every minute" |
| `interval: 60` | "every hour" |
| `interval: 1440` | "every day" |
| `interval: n` | "every n minutes" / "every n hours" |
| `cron: "…"` | raw cron string (future: human parse) |

### `format-remote.ts`

**`shortenRemoteUrl(url)`** — strips `https://`, `git@`, and `.git` suffix for display. Both `https://github.com/user/repo.git` and `git@github.com:user/repo.git` → `github.com/user/repo`.

